Hi Parent_B—happy to answer.

(1) Settling-in / transition (first 2–3 weeks):
- We use a gradual, child-centered approach. In week 1, we typically start with shorter days (or a shorter morning block) and build up as your child shows comfort.
- We assign a consistent key educator to help your child form a secure relationship quickly.
- We keep routines predictable (same arrival rhythm, visual cues, consistent goodbye routine) and coordinate closely with you on what helps (comfort item, preferred soothing strategies).
- We’ll share brief daily notes during the transition period so you know how eating, mood, play engagement, and separation are going.

(2) Naps + outdoor time (timing & flexibility):
- Outdoor time: daily, usually late morning and/or mid-afternoon depending on weather and the group’s energy. We’re flexible—if a group is especially regulated by outdoor play, we prioritize it.
- Nap/rest: after lunch. Younger children who need longer sleep are accommodated; older children who don’t nap have a quiet rest period and then calm activities (books, puzzles, table work) so the room stays restful.
- We adjust expectations by age and individual needs (e.g., easing into the full rest routine during the first weeks).

To make sure we’re a strong match: how old is your child, and are naps currently consistent at home (duration/timing)? If Nursery_E is becoming a serious option for you, an application as soon as you’re ready is helpful since we only have limited space this cycle.
